result.name: Man Fong Cafe

reviews.text: Foods good ,especially roast chicken wing
The decoration is good. Unfortunately the good is not. It seems they ve forgotten the primary value of a restaurant.

A small local tea shop(café) with a history in the New Territories for about 55 years. There is nothing special about it save for some old reprinted photos in the shop that would attract those looking for a sense of nostalgia.
Have a quick breakfast or lunch at a relatively low price and go when you finish as you are not welcome if you stay long.

Been here twice.  It has a vibe of old hongkong style restaurant (cha chaan teng) but very clean. It resembles a historic part of Hong Kong culture, although it has been remodeled. They have nostalgic photographs from the last couple decades of Hong Kong as decorations on the wall. 
Service was fast. Price was fairly cheap and reasonable with large food portions. Flavor was average and not bad. I went after rush lunch hour, so it wasn’t too crowded. I might visit for the third time if have the chance. 
The AC was very cold and windy — suggest to bring a cardigan if you do not want to catch a cold.
not bad but heavy MSG
